  {
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "I am down for using a cleanup method instead rather than introducing IDs and making the state manager aware of those IDS. We may need this in the future but right now I don't think this is needed.\r\n\r\nThe reasoning behind using a cleanup method like this:\r\n\r\n```js\r\ncleanup: function(state) {\r\n  return omit(state, attributeName);\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nrather than having to specify an ID in a connector is that it's more in line with the way connectors need to handle the state today. They need to handle it fully (in refine methods)\r\n\r\nI see IDs and automatic cleaning of IDs a bit magical and doing things in the background (in state manager) that are sometime being done in the foreground (in the connector, in refine).",
    "created_at": "2016-11-22T15:16:30Z",
